inversed is used to find the angle

When solving for an angle, we use the inverse trigonometric ratio because (in this situation) what we have is x and y. If you've studied the Unit Circle in Trig, then you know that tangent is equal to y divided by x. So, if we have an x value and a y value, and we divide them, that would be the tangent value. Since we're solving for an angle, we need to take the inverse tangent to "undo" the tangent in our equation "Tangent of angle θ is equal to y/x" since we're not solving for x or y.
